The chief press secretary to the INEC chairman, Mr. Rotimi Oyekanmi told journalists early Saturday morning that the commission has reached a decision on whether the Presidential and National Assembly elections will go ahead or not. He spoke briefly with journalists after he came out of the emergency meeting at the national headquarters of the commission in Abuja. Oyekanmi said INEC chairman, Prof Mahmoud Yakubu. will make formal announcement shortly.  Details later… No plan to postpone 2019 Elections – INEC Governorship/State assembly elections: INEC’s final list excludes APC candidates in Zamfara, Rivers Issues as  INEC prepares ahead of 2019